  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3889091930" />
    <a title="Swaroop" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100264072-swaroop"><img alt="Swaroop" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621672092p2/100264072.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3889091930?book_show_action=true">Mar 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Swaroop" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Swaroop" href="/user/show/100264072-swaroop">Swaroop</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780061252020" href="/book/show/862816.Fragile_Things">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3889091930" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2385608310176646702">Strange, crazy, dark, imaginative, thought-provoking, fun and twisted. <br/><br/><i>&quot;It occurs to me that the peculiarity of the most things that we think of as fragile, is of tough they truly are.&quot;</i><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1618080769i/31159846.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Neil Gaiman`s Fragile Things is not the best of Gaiman, but is still interesting because it is Gaiman!<br/> 😊 This collection of short stories and few lines of poetry won the 2007 Locus Award for Best Collection and was nominated for a Hugo Award. <br/> <br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1618080769i/31159847.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>This collection also gives a good understanding of the thinking process</span>
  <span id="freeText2385608310176646702" style="display:none">Strange, crazy, dark, imaginative, thought-provoking, fun and twisted. <br><br><i>"It occurs to me that the peculiarity of the most things that we think of as fragile, is of tough they truly are."</i><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1618080769i/31159846.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Neil Gaiman`s Fragile Things is not the best of Gaiman, but is still interesting because it is Gaiman!<br> 😊 This collection of short stories and few lines of poetry won the 2007 Locus Award for Best Collection and was nominated for a Hugo Award. <br> <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1618080769i/31159847.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>This collection also gives a good understanding of the thinking process of Neil Gaiman – demonstrates how diverse, complicated, comical and out-of-the-ordinary his mind works! It also proves that he never disappoints… <br><br>***<br><i>Even ashes can give up their secrets<br>==========<br>He was born with a runny nose, and it never stopped running<br>==========<br>What's it like being dead!?<br>==========<br>"We owe it to each other to tell stories."<br>==========<br>"I put the stresses at the wrong places." </i><br></span>
